%I A316194 #25 Jun 20 2026 22:57:11
%S A316194 0,1,1,3,4,16,23,87,128,485,739,2798,4352,16507,26132,99302
%N A316194 Number of symmetric self-avoiding polygons on square lattice with perimeter 2*n, not counting rotations and reflections as distinct.
%C A316194 The sequence includes polygons of 2-fold, i.e., mirror or rotational, and higher (order >= 4) symmetry.
%C A316194 From _Anton Pirogov_, Jun 17 2026: (Start)
%C A316194 Also number of symmetric simple matchstick polygons on the cyclotomic ring Z[zeta_4].
%C A316194 Terms a(9)-a(16) (perimeters 18..32) were obtained as a sub-count of the free enumeration of simple matchstick polygons on Z[zeta_4] using the tilezz library. (End)
%H A316194 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="http://www.randomwalk.de/sequences/a316194.htm">Illustration of polygons of perimeter <= 16</a>.
%H A316194 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz">tilezz</a> - exact cyclotomic geometry library including a polygon enumerator.
%H A316194 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://ratdb.app.pirogov.de">Rat Explorer</a> - interactive database of cyclotomic matchstick polygons.
%H A316194 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz-ratdb">RatDB datasets</a> - reproducible datasets containing the enumerated polygons.
%Y A316194 Cf. A002931, A266549, A316196, A323188, A323189.
%K A316194 nonn,walk,more,changed
